## Complete workflow

```powershell
# 1. Create branch
git checkout -b feature/my-feature

# 2. Make changes, run targeted tests
.venv\Scripts\pytest.exe tests/affected/test_file.py -v

# 3. Run full lint — required, not optional, run it now in this session
./make.ps1 lint

# 4. Commit — subject line counted to <= 72 chars, two -m flags
git commit -m "Short subject line under 72 chars" -m "Body explaining why and how, covering all meaningful sub-changes."

# 5. Push
git push origin feature/my-feature
```

